# 4. Detailed Process Flow – Lead Capture

## Objective

Capture customer inquiries from multiple channels and create lead records in Salesforce.

### Process Flow

```text
Customer Submits Inquiry
        │
        ▼
System Receives Data
        │
        ▼
Validate Mandatory Fields
        │
        ├───────────── No ─────────────► Display Validation Error
        │
       Yes
        │
        ▼
Check Duplicate Records
        │
        ├──────────── Duplicate Found ───────────► Display Existing Lead
        │
        ▼
Create Lead Record
        │
        ▼
Set Status = New
        │
        ▼
Trigger Assignment Process
```

### Inputs

* Customer Name
* Email Address
* Mobile Number
* Preferred Vehicle
* Lead Source

### Outputs

* Salesforce Lead Record
* Lead ID Generated

---

# 5. Detailed Process Flow – Lead Assignment

## Objective

Assign leads automatically to the most appropriate sales representative.

### Process Flow

```text
Lead Created
        │
        ▼
Identify Dealership Branch
        │
        ▼
Evaluate Assignment Rules
        │
        ▼
Check Representative Availability
        │
        ├──────── No Available Rep ───────► Assign To Sales Manager
        │
       Yes
        │
        ▼
Assign Lead
        │
        ▼
Send Notification
        │
        ▼
Update Lead Owner
```

### Assignment Criteria

1. Branch Location
2. Vehicle Category
3. Representative Availability
4. Round-Robin Distribution

### Output

Assigned Lead Record

---

# 6. Detailed Process Flow – Lead Qualification

## Objective

Determine customer purchase intent and readiness.

### Process Flow

```text
Lead Assigned
        │
        ▼
Sales Representative Reviews Lead
        │
        ▼
Contact Customer
        │
        ▼
Collect Customer Requirements
        │
        ▼
Evaluate Qualification Criteria
        │
        ├──────── Not Qualified ─────────► Lead Nurturing Process
        │
       Qualified
        │
        ▼
Update Lead Status
        │
        ▼
Create Follow-Up Activity
        │
        ▼
Proceed To Test Drive Scheduling
```

### Qualification Factors

* Budget Availability
* Purchase Timeline
* Vehicle Interest
* Customer Engagement

### Output

Qualified Lead

